Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of web accessibility tests.

Ten different tools (Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE) tested the web page of Member Al Muratsuchi (D) at https://a66.asmdc.org/ to check its compliance with various rules. There were a total of about 1350 rules, classified into about 250 accessibility issues.

The results were interpreted to yield an aggregate score of 1291, where 0 would be perfect.

Total score

The total score is the sum of five components.

Score summary
ComponentScoreDescription
total1291Sum of the component scores
issue1083Severity and number of reported defects
tool168Tool-by-tool defect ratings
prevention0Failed attempts by tools to test the page
log40Browser warnings about the page
latency0Abnormal delay in page responses

The score of an issue depends on the severity (user impact and certainty) of the issue and on how many instances were reported (by one or more tools).
